cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SY

The paper discusses the application of information theory in analyzing complex systems, particularly in neural spiking data. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the differences between multivariate information measures, which may fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper applies the information measures to model systems and neural spiking data, which may fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
